      • getUrlStringFromBytes

        protected static java.lang.String getUrlStringFromBytes(byte[] bytes)
        Returns the Eddystone url string based on the byte array as it is encoded in the Eddystone URL message. The byte array must be ordered in big endian.
        Parameters:
        bytes - the byte array as specified in the Eddystone URL message.
        Returns:
        the URL that is encoded in the byte array.

      • getUrlBytesFromString

        protected static byte[] getUrlBytesFromString(java.lang.String urlString)
                                       throws EddystoneUrlMessage.WrongUrlFormatException
        Returns a byte array of the url string in big endian order.
        Parameters:
        urlString - The eddystone url.
        Returns:
        byte array as it is specified in the Eddystone format.
        Throws:
        EddystoneUrlMessage.WrongUrlFormatException - will be thrown, if the URL is illegal.
